{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "TDD — Run Tests After Code Changes",
  "description": "Enforces TDD workflow for shared-libs monorepo: after editing Python source or test files in any sub-package, run that sub-package's tests immediately.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "**/src/**/*.py",
      "**/tests/**/*.py"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "You just edited a Python file in the shared-libs monorepo. Follow the TDD workflow:\n\n1. Identify which sub-package was changed (auth-client, event-lib, logging-lib, or testing-lib) from the file path.\n\n2. If you wrote a TEST file: run it with `uv run pytest <test_file>::<test_name> -v` using cwd set to the sub-package directory (e.g., `ugsys-shared-libs/auth-client`) — it should FAIL (RED).\n\n3. If you wrote a SOURCE file: run the corresponding test with `uv run pytest tests/ -v --tb=short` using cwd set to the sub-package directory — it should now PASS (GREEN).\n\n4. NEVER skip running tests. NEVER write more implementation without a failing test first.\n\nAlways use cwd pointing to the specific sub-package directory, NOT the shared-libs root."
  }
}
